noun.description: An ornamental frame around the top and sides of a door, window, or fireplace.

origin: Late 17th century. From French chambranle, probably an alteration of chambrande from an unattested post-classical Latin form *camerandus or its neuter singular *camerandum, use as noun of gerundive of post-classical Latin camerare, thus lit. something which must be arched. See further Trésor de la langue française at cited word.
